# Implementation Plan - DEG-FLOW Upgrade (2024-2026 Standards)

This plan upgrades the [ActiveOptions](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l3_assembly/presenters/ui/active_options/presenter.py#66-176) engine to use institutional-grade microstructure metrics, replacing simple Z-Score sorting with an "Impact Index" and adding clustering-aware flow recognition.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Sorting Change**: The "Active Options" list will now be sorted by **Impact Index** (Flow $\times$ Gamma $\times$ Decay) rather than just Flow Z-Score. This may change which options appear at the top, especially near market close.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Options Flow Engines (L2)

#### [MODIFY] [flow_engine.py](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/shared/models/flow_engine.py)
- Update [FlowEngineOutput](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/shared/models/flow_engine.py#93-126) to include `impact_index: float`.

#### [MODIFY] [flow_engine_g.py](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l2_decision/signals/flow/flow_engine_g.py)
- **Tick-by-tick Flow Concept**: Enhance the flow calculation to use a "Turnover Velocity" factor as a proxy for aggressive labeling.
- $FlowG = \Delta OI \times IV_{norm} \times Turnover \times \text{VelocityBoost}$.

#### [MODIFY] [deg_composer.py](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l2_decision/signals/flow/deg_composer.py)
- **Option Activity Clustering**: Implement a correction pass after Z-Score normalization.
- If multiple nearby strikes ($\pm 2$) show high Z-Scores, apply a reinforcement multiplier ($1.25x$) to signify an "Institutional Sweep".

---

### [Component] UI Presenter (L3)

#### [MODIFY] [presenter.py](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l3_assembly/presenters/ui/active_options/presenter.py)
- **Impact Index Calculation**: Implement $OFII = \frac{|Flow_{USD}| \times |\Gamma| \times e^{-\tau}}{MarketDepth}$.
- **Sorting**: Change `top = sorted(outputs, key=lambda o: abs(o.flow_deg), reverse=True)` to sort by `impact_index`.
- Include `impact_index` in the final UI payload for frontend debugging.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Create `tests/l2_decision/test_flow_engine_upgrades.py`:
  - `test_clustering_correction`: Verify Z-Score reinforcement when 3+ strikes are active.
  - `test_impact_index_sorting`: Ensure high-gamma "Impact" options rank higher than high-volume but "No-Gamma" options.
- Run tests via `pytest tests/l2_decision/test_flow_engine_upgrades.py`.

### Manual Verification
1. Start the system via [.\scripts\infra\redis-start.bat](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/scripts/infra/redis-start.bat) and `npm run dev`.
2. Open the browser and navigate to the Active Options widget.
3. Observe if the list correctly identifies clustered "Institutional Sweeps" (Visual check for high-Z groups).
